.TH "nvmf_context_create" 9 "nvmf_context_create" "March 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvmf_context_create \- Create a new fabrics context for discovery/connect
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nvmf_context_create
.BI "(struct nvme_global_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "bool (*decide_retry)(struct nvmf_context *fctx, int err, void *user_data) "  ","
.BI "void (*connected)(struct nvmf_context *fctx, struct nvme_ctrl *c, void *user_data) "  ","
.BI "void (*already_connected)(struct nvmf_context *fctx, struct nvme_host *host, const char *subsysnqn, const char *transport, const char *traddr, const char *trsvcid, void *user_data) "  ","
.BI "void *user_data "  ","
.BI "struct nvmf_context **fctxp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
Global context
.IP "decide_retry" 12
Callback to decide if a retry should be attempted
.IP "connected" 12
Callback invoked when a connection is established
.IP "already_connected" 12
Callback invoked if already connected
.IP "user_data" 12
User data passed to callbacks
.IP "fctxp" 12
Pointer to store the created context
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates and initializes a new fabrics context for discovery/connect
operations.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or a negative error code on failure.
